Process called "estimate_hot_paths_with_heuristics" that takes code as BytecodeBlock returns List[Integer]:
    Try:
        Let hot_paths be list containing
        
        For each block in code.basic_blocks:
            Let hotness_score be calculate_block_hotness_heuristic with block as block
            If hotness_score is greater than 0.7:
                Add block.block_id to hot_paths
        
        Let sorted_hot_paths be sort_by_hotness with paths as hot_paths and code as code
        Return sorted_hot_paths
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Note: Advanced Optimization Helper Functions
Process called \"find_highest_priority_pass\" that takes passes as List[OptimizationPass] returns OptimizationPass:\n    Let highest_priority_pass be passes at index 0\n    Let highest_priority be highest_priority_pass.priority\n    \n    For each pass in passes:\n        If pass.priority is less than highest_priority:\n            Set highest_priority to pass.priority\n            Set highest_priority_pass to pass\n    \n    Return highest_priority_pass

Process called \"find_block_by_id\" that takes blocks as List[BasicBlock] and id as Integer returns Optional[BasicBlock]:\n    For each block in blocks:\n        If block.block_id is equal to id:\n            Return block\n    Return None

Process called \"calculate_block_hotness_heuristic\" that takes block as BasicBlock returns Float:\n    Let base_hotness be block.execution_frequency\n    Let loop_bonus be 0.2 if block.loop_info is not None else 0.0\n    Return (base_hotness plus loop_bonus) clamped between 0.0 and 1.0

Process called \"sort_by_hotness\" that takes paths as List[Integer] and code as BytecodeBlock returns List[Integer]:\n    Return paths